<Layout
  title="Types of Commercial Doors: Choosing the Right One for Your Business"
  description="Explore the different types of commercial doors — from automatic sliding to fire-rated and security doors — and learn which is best for your business in Orlando, Miami, or Denver."
  keywords="types of commercial doors, automatic doors, security doors, fire-rated doors, storefront doors, commercial door installation, Orlando, Miami, Denver"
>
  <section class="relative bg-primary text-white py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-primary/95 to-primary/70"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 mb-2"><a href="/blog" class="hover:text-white underline">Blog</a> / Types of Commercial Doors</p>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-wide mb-4">Types of Commercial Doors: Choosing the Right One for Your Business</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Published March 10, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 prose prose-lg">
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Selecting the right commercial door is one of the most important decisions a business owner can make. The door you choose affects security, energy efficiency, accessibility, and the overall appearance of your property. With so many options available, it helps to understand what each type offers before making an investment.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4 mt-10">Automatic Sliding Doors</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Automatic sliding doors are a popular choice for retail stores, medical facilities, and office buildings. They provide hands-free access, making them ideal for high-traffic environments and ADA compliance. These doors use motion sensors to open and close smoothly, reducing wear on the door system and improving energy efficiency by minimizing the time the entrance is open. Professional <a href="/service/commercial-door-installation" class="text-accent hover:underline">commercial door installation</a> ensures proper sensor calibration and track alignment.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4 mt-10">Security Doors</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Security doors are built with reinforced steel or aluminum and are designed to resist forced entry. They are essential for warehouses, storage facilities, and any business that handles valuable inventory. Many security doors feature integrated <a href="/service/commercial-door-lock-services" class="text-accent hover:underline">commercial lock systems</a> with electronic access controls, key card readers, or biometric scanners. These doors provide peace of mind and are an investment in protecting your assets.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4 mt-10">Fire-Rated Doors</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Fire-rated doors are required by building codes in many commercial settings. They are constructed to withstand fire for a specified period, typically ranging from 20 minutes to 3 hours, helping to contain fires and protect escape routes. These doors must be properly installed and maintained to meet code requirements. Regular inspections of <a href="/service/hinge-repair-replacement" class="text-accent hover:underline">hinges</a>, closers, and seals are critical to ensure fire-rated doors function as intended during an emergency.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4 mt-10">Aluminum Storefront Doors</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Aluminum storefront doors are lightweight, durable, and offer a clean, modern look. They are commonly used in retail spaces, restaurants, and professional offices. Available with full glass panels for maximum visibility, these doors create an inviting entrance while still providing structural strength. The aluminum frames resist corrosion, making them a practical choice for businesses in humid climates like <a href="/location/commercial-door-services-miami" class="text-accent hover:underline">Miami</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4 mt-10">Rolling Steel Doors</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Rolling steel doors, also known as roll-up doors, are widely used in loading docks, warehouses, and parking garages. They offer excellent security and are space-efficient because they roll up overhead rather than swinging out. Over time, the <a href="/service/roller-replacement-and-frame-repair" class="text-accent hover:underline">rollers and frames</a> on these doors can wear down, so regular maintenance is essential to avoid costly breakdowns.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4 mt-10">Hollow Metal Doors</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Hollow metal doors are a versatile and cost-effective option for interior and exterior commercial applications. They are commonly found in stairwells, utility rooms, and back-of-house areas. These doors are available in various gauges to meet different security and durability requirements. When properly maintained with timely <a href="/service/lock-repair" class="text-accent hover:underline">lock repairs</a> and hardware adjustments, hollow metal doors provide years of reliable service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4 mt-10">How to Choose the Right Door</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The best commercial door for your business depends on several factors: the level of security you need, local building codes, your budget, the amount of foot traffic, and the aesthetic you want to achieve. Consulting with an experienced <a href="/service/commercial-door-installation" class="text-accent hover:underline">commercial door installation</a> team can help you weigh these factors and select a door that meets all your requirements.
      </p>

